# Model disclosure

## First reply of a new chat

In the **very first** reply of each new conversation, start with a model disclosure:

- If available: `Running on model X (provider Y)`.
- If not available: `The exact model name / provider is not available to me.`

Put it at the **beginning** of the first reply only. Do not bury it in the middle or end. Do not repeat it in later replies of the same chat.

## Grok and Composer (any version)

If the session runs on **Grok** or **Composer** (any version), one disclosure at the start of the new chat is enough.

- Do **not** repeat the disclosure later in the same chat.
- Do **not** notify about version switches within the same family (e.g. Grok 4.5 → another Grok, Composer → another Composer) unless the user asks.

## Other models / real provider change

If the underlying model or provider changes to something **outside** the Grok/Composer family (or becomes unknown), in the **very next** reply inform the user, for example:

- `The model has changed to Y`
- `The provider has changed to Z`

Do not skip that notification.
